# Greptile Review Protocol

When addressing Greptile inline comments on a PR, after fixing each issue, post a reply to that comment on GitHub using the `gh api` command to indicate the fix has been applied.

## How to reply to a PR review comment

```bash
gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/comments/{comment_id}/replies \
  --method POST \
  --field body="Fixed in {commit_sha}: {one-line description of what was done}"
```

To find comment IDs:
```bash
gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{pr_number}/comments | python3 -c "
import json, sys
for c in json.load(sys.stdin):
    print(c['id'], c['path'], c.get('line','?'), c['body'][:80])
"
```

## What the reply should say

- Reference the commit SHA where the fix was made
- One sentence describing what changed
- Example: `"Fixed in cf56d64: updated regex to capture 1-2 words and added _resolve_team() for two-word city name lookup"`
